    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I can't find a place in `libp2p` to differentiate dialer and listener. My approach is to override libp2p `dialProtocol` and maintain a `dials` set in our libp2p in order to differentiate it.\r\n+ In `dialProtocol`, add peer-info/peer-id to `dials` set\r\n+ On \"peer:connect\", if the peerInfo is in `dials` set then emit \"peer:outbound:connected\", otherwise emit \"peer:inbound:connected\"\r\n+ On \"peer:disconnect\", remove the peerInfo/peer id from `dials` list\r\n\r\nWhat do you think?",
